 jambonz-rtpengine-utils,
Description: proxy for RTP and media streams (jambonz build)
 This daemon handles the first stages of proxying media streams and talks to
 the kernel part of the proxy for eventual high-performance packet forwarding.
 .
 jambonz fork of sipwise/rtpengine. Differs from upstream in package naming
 only — same source code, same DKMS kernel module, same hardened systemd unit.

Package: jambonz-rtpengine-dkms
Architecture: all
Section: kernel
Depends:
 ${misc:Depends},
Description: nftables kernel module for jambonz-rtpengine - DKMS
 Provides the kernel-space part of the rtpengine media proxy for high-
 performance packet forwarding. This package contains the kernel module
 source to be built via DKMS, so it auto-rebuilds against any new kernel
 the host installs.

